The aim of the study is to evaluate whether patients with early equivocal appendicitis can be observed instead of immediate diagnostic imaging.

 Half of the patients are randomly assigned to observation group, while the other half will undergo diagnostic imaging.

 The hypothesis is that resolving appendicitis is common in these patients.

 Thus, in observation group there will be fewer patients with appendicitis diagnosis and observation reduces the use of diagnostic imaging and surgery.

